subject: [Bad] *Changing Terms* on Kippt.com: may change their privacy policy without prior notice
text:
Here is the concern:
«Although most changes are likely to be minor, Kippt may change its Privacy Policy from time to time, and in Kippt’s sole discretion. Kippt encourages visitors to frequently check this page for any changes to its Privacy Policy. Your continued use of this site after any change in this Privacy Policy will constitute your acceptance of such change.»
Here are the ToS:
https://kippt.com/privacy/

As Hugo say, «just posting an announcement on the site isn't enough IMHO for material 
changes. At least a notice by email should be considered best practice». But Kippt:
1. may change its privacy policy without prior notice 
2. consider you to have accepted if you continue to use the service!!!

Chy!

V
